# API Test Automation with RestAssured

This project demonstrates API automation testing using **RestAssured** for testing RESTful services. In this example, we are fetching random cat facts through a public API and validating the response.

## Project Setup

### Prerequisites
Before running the tests, ensure you have the following installed:
- Java 8 or higher
- Maven
- IDE (IntelliJ IDEA, Eclipse, etc.)

## Getting Started

### 1. Clone the Repository
Clone the repository to your local machine using Git:
git clone https://github.com/your-username/api-test-automation.git

2. Run the Tests

3. View Test Reports
TestNG generates a detailed HTML report located in the /test-output directory after the tests are complete.